  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Executive - Freight",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong><br /><br />We are seeking a driven and experienced <strong>Sales Executive</strong> to lead freight operations and drive business growth in the <strong>Project Cargo Logistics</strong> sector. This role is ideal for a high-performing sales professional with deep industry knowledge, strong client engagement skills, and a hunter mentality. You will be responsible for expanding our customer base, managing key accounts, and orchestrating logistics solutions that meet complex supply chain needs.</p><p><strong>Main Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Drive freight operations and business development for project cargo logistics.</p></li><li><p>Achieve revenue targets and acquire new and potential accounts.</p></li><li><p>Maintain consistent engagement with clients to ensure ongoing participation and satisfaction.</p></li><li><p>Manage and grow existing clientele while actively hunting for new business opportunities.</p></li><li><p>Lead customer presentations and proposals with professionalism and strategic insight.</p></li><li><p>Share market intelligence on customer needs and competitor developments with internal stakeholders.</p></li><li><p>Contribute to the enhancement of sales best practices and strategic account management.</p></li><li><p>Arrange, coordinate, and follow up on shipments to ensure smooth execution.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Education</strong>: Minimum Diploma, preferably in Logistics, Supply Chain, or Marketing.</p></li><li><p><strong>Experience</strong>: At least 3-5 years of sales experience in Freight Forwarding.</p></li><li><p><strong>Skills & Attributes</strong>:</p><ul><li><p>Strong hunter acumen and proactive sales approach.</p></li><li><p>Solid understanding of supply chain operations and ability to align solutions with business offerings.</p></li><li><p>Excellent communication and presentation skills.</p></li></ul></li></ul>",
